table.name: generator
table.comment: Identifies power generator associated with FACILITY.

column.name: genid
column.comment: Public identifier used for GENERATOR as reported to EIA and for New Unit Exemption purposes.

column.name: arp_nameplate_capacity
column.comment: Design nameplate capacity, in megawatts, of the GENERATOR.

column.name: other_nameplate_capacity
column.comment: Nameplate capacity, in megawatts, of the GENERATOR as applicable to other programs such as CAIR.

column.name: utility_ind
column.comment: Identifies whether a GENERATOR is a utility or a non-utility.

column.name: prime_mover_type_cd
column.comment: Type, such as combined cycle, steam turbine, etc., of a GENERATOR.

column.name: gen_capacity_factor
column.comment: Capacity factor based on actual operations.

column.name: online_year
column.comment: Four digit year that the GENERATOR came online.

column.name: eia_year
column.comment: The year for which EIA identification information is provided.

column.name: userid
column.comment: The user name of the person or process that created the record if the Update Date is empty. Otherwise this is the user name of the person or process that made the last update.

column.name: update_date
column.comment: Date of the last record update.

table.name: accuracy_spec_code
table.comment: Lookup table for accuracy specification code.

column.name: accuracy_spec_cd
column.comment: Unique code value for a lookup table.
